Title : Orustdalen
Text : '''Orustdalen''' is a valley in [[Nordenskiöld Land]] at [[Spitsbergen]], [[Svalbard]]. It is named after Swedish island of [[Orust]] in the province of [[Bohuslän]]. The valley has a length of about five kilometers and a width of two kilometers. It is located south of the mountains of [[Qvigstadfjellet]], [[Christensenfjella]] and [[Systemafjellet]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Orustdalen |title=Orustdalen (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Arctic Pilot: Sailing directions Svalbard&ndash;Jan Mayen |year=1988 | volume =7 |publisher=The Norwegian Hydrographic Service and The Norwegian Polar Institute |location=Stavanger |language= |isbn=82-90653-06-9 |pages=217&ndash;218}}  </ref>

